'''Galen Torg''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Alderaanian/Legends|native]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]], who served as a military [[Officer/Legends|officer]] on his [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]]. By some point surrounding his planet's [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destruction]] by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|DS-1 Orbital Battle Station]] in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], Torg joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], and retained his ceremonial dress uniform during his service. That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], the Alliance managed to [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|destroy]] the DS-1 Orbital Battle Station in the [[Yavin system/Legends|Yavin system]]. Torg was selected to serve as a [[Rebel Honor Guard/Legends|Rebel Honor Guard]] sentry for the [[Royal Award Ceremony/Legends|ceremony]] held to honor the [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|Heroes of Yavin]] at the [[Great Temple/Legends|Alliance's headquarters]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]].

==Biography==
The [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="ANH" /> [[Gender/Legends|male]] Galen Torg<ref name="GG1" /> [[Alderaanian/Legends|hailed]] from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]]<ref name="Honor Guard note" /> during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], a conflict between the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="ANH" /> At some point by [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> Torg served as a military [[Officer/Legends|officer]] on Alderaan.<ref name="Honor Guard note" /> That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], the Empire used their [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|DS-1 Orbital Battle Station]] [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]]&mdash;code named the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]]&mdash;to [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destroy]] Torg's [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]].<ref name="NEC" /> Torg was among the surviving Alderaanians, and also retained<ref name="Honor Guard note" /> his<ref name="CCG" /> ceremonial dress uniform. By then, he had also joined the Alliance, and continued to use his uniform in the Alliance.<ref name="Honor Guard note" />

In 0 BBY, the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] occurred, during which the Alliance's [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] destroyed the Death Star in the [[Yavin system/Legends|Yavin system]].<ref name="NEC" /> Following the battle, a [[Royal Award Ceremony/Legends|ceremony]] was held in the [[Grand Audience Chamber]] of the [[Great Temple/Legends|Great Temple]], the Alliance's [[Alliance High Command/Legends|headquarters]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. Torg was among the [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]]<ref name="ANH" /> selected<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=Rebel Guard}}</ref> to serve as [[Rebel Honor Guard/Legends|Rebel Honor Guard]] sentries for the occasion. Torg stood in front of the Chamber's entrance during the ceremony, which honored the [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|Heroes of Yavin]]: [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]].<ref name="ANH" />

==Personality and traits==
Galen Torg was loyal to the Rebellion,<ref name="GG1" /> and typical of the Alliance's hard-working, unsung heroes.<ref name="CCG" /> As a survivor of Alderaan,<ref name="Honor Guard note" /> and as a reward for his dedication and courage, he was selected<ref name="BtM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref> to serve as part of the honor guard at the award ceremony as thanks for the Heroes of Yavin's destruction of the Death Star.<ref name="Honor Guard note" /> Torg stood at a height of 1.8 [[Meter/Legends|meters]]<ref name="GG1" /> and had fair skin.<ref name="ANH" />

==Equipment==
Torg wielded an [[Electropole/Legends|electropole]],<ref name="ANH" /> along with a [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]] and [[Grenade/Legends|grenades]].<!--Respectively damage 4D and 5D, I personally have no reason to take them as anything more than game mechanics.--> He also owned a [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]] and a pair of [[Macrobinoculars/Legends|macrobinoculars]].<ref name="GG1" />

==Behind the scenes==
Galen Torg first appeared as an uncredited honor guard extra visible during the ending award ceremony scene of [[1977]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="ANH" /> In [[1989]], the first edition of [[West End Games]]' ''[[Galaxy Guide 1: A New Hope]]'' sourcebook mentioned the name "Galen Torg" as an example of a standard Rebel soldier for use with ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'', providing him mainly [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] statistics. The book did not establish that Torg was any Rebel character who appeared in ''A New Hope''.<ref name="GG1" /> In [[1995]], the ''[[Premiere Limited]]'' edition of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]] was the first source to identify Galen Torg as one of the honor guard extras seen at the end of the film.<ref name="CCG" />

===Non-canon content===
A re-imagining of the award ceremony which included sentries standing at the entrance was included in the [[2006]] [[Infinities|non-canon]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[LEGO Star Wars II: The Original Trilogy]]'', along with 2007's ''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Complete Saga]]''. However, their uniforms are the uniforms of [[Rebel trooper/Legends|Rebel troopers]] belonging to the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]], as opposed to the [[canon]]ical Honor Guard uniforms.<ref name="Lego OT">''[[LEGO Star Wars II: The Original Trilogy]]''</ref><ref name="Lego Complete">''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Complete Saga]]''</ref>

